      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n14\nNeeds Review\n14\n14 my writing - such as \"Ubik\" - reveal deep Hegelian dialectical anti - theist philosophy, which Lem etal noted. What I regard as Gnosticism is an anti estab‐ lishment-Xtianity anti-theist view (that of an irrational deity, or world, as in \"Valis\") in which rationality comes into existence - by a dialectical historic process of evolution This is Hegelian! The whole concept of Valis is rooted in dialectical materialistic mysticism T",
